The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 Luxembourg, May 13: ArcelorMittal chief executive Lakshmi Mittal has become the chairman of the company. Two years after the end of the takeover battle that finally led to the purchase of Arcelor by Mittal Steel, Mittal achieved his ambition of leading a company that produces over 100 million tonnes of steel a year and is about three times bigger than its nearest rival.                            
	 Mumbai, May 13: The Securities Appellate Tribunal has upheld a Sebi order, which found company secretary and chief financial officer of Wockhardt Rajiv Gandhi and two others guilty of insider trading.                            
	 New Delhi, May 13: The Central Board of Excise and Customs (CBEC) has exceeded its target by 42 per cent in recovering arrears of revenue fixed for the 2007-08 fiscal. Against the target of Rs 3,550 crore, the department has collected Rs 5,035 crore.                            
	 New Delhi, May 13: Bharti Airtel today said it has not made any bid to acquire South Africas MTN. Bharti would like to clarify that it has not made any bid, nor is there any requirement to make a bid, as has been incorrectly speculated and reported, the company said in a statement here.                            
	 New Delhi, May 13: Persons and firms with a low capital of Rs 1 lakh can act as corporate agents of insurance companies and sell policies through their agents, if the IRDA accepts the recommendations of a report on distribution channels. The present limit (of Rs 15 lakh) is very onerous and the limit of one lakh proposed is reasonable, said the report.                            
	 Mumbai, May 13: Preferential allotments have emerged as the most favoured route for raising funds from primary markets by corporates, which during 2007-08 mobilised Rs 1.74 lakh crore, stated a Sebi bulletin.                            
	 New Delhi, May 13: Tata Motors said it would consider exporting the Rs 1-lakh car to promising markets including the US.                                                                                                                                
